717627f-b.title: Manhattan: Broadway - Amsterdam Avenue
717627f-b.text:
Broadwey, north from West 72nd Street, as photographed
across the triangular park that is formed by it's intersec-
tion with Amsterdam Avenue. Shown prominently is the ornate
Ansonia, an apartment hotel that occupies the entire west
frontage from 73rd to 74th Street's. This is detailed in
View No. 2. The Central Savings Bank extends from 73rd to
74th Street's between the aforementioned thoroughfares.
July 1930
March 1934
George L. Balgue
